-- Turkey’s Ulker May Buy Some Rainford Assets, Mergermarket Says
-- B y   B e n j a m i n   H a r v e y
-- 2012-06-14T06:53:16Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-14/turkey-s-ulker-may-buy-some-rainford-assets-mergermarket-says.html
Ulker Biskuvi Sanayi AS (ULKER) , Turkey’s
largest sweets maker, is in talks with Ukraine’s Rainford Group
to buy its confectionary assets, Mergermarket reported, citing
two people close to the situation that it didn’t name.  The talks may be concluded within a month, and Ulker may
spend more than $600 million on acquisitions this year,
Mergermarket said citing one of the people.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Benjamin Harvey in Istanbul at 
